{
  "texts": [
    "I. INTRODUCTIONThe Global Cancer Observatory reported in 2020 that the incidence of liver cancer accounted for approximately 905,000 cases worldwide [1].",
    "Percutaneous liver biopsy is considered the gold-standard technique to diagnose hepatic lesions [2].",
    "Ultrasound (US) or computed-tomography (CT) scans are usually used to guide physicians throughout the insertion [3].",
    "US provides real-time guidance without ionizing radiation [4].",
    "However, there is high interoperator variability and the spatial resolution is limited [5]."
  ]
}